# access-manager-ui — Cursor Rules

Read `AGENTS.md` for full context. These rules are the distilled version for inline guidance.

## Repository layout

- `src/api/` — client.ts (fetch wrapper) + one file per entity (domains.ts, users.ts, …)
- `src/pages/` — route-level components (thin, no business logic)
- `src/hooks/` — TanStack Query hooks and mutation wrappers
- `src/components/` — shared UI (shadcn/ui components copied here)
- `src/lib/` — pure utilities (cn(), etc.)

## Layer boundary (enforce strictly)

Pages → Hooks → `api/*.ts` named functions → `api/client.ts`

- Never import `api/client.ts` directly in a page or hook
- Never import React in `api/client.ts` or `api/*.ts`
- No business logic in JSX — extract to hooks or helpers

## Security

- Never write secrets, tokens, or API keys in source code
- `.env.local` is gitignored; reference `.env.example` for variable names
- `VITE_API_BEARER_TOKEN` lives in env only — never hardcoded

## No unused code

- Do not add uncalled functions or components
- Defer speculative additions to a GitHub issue
- Mark future work: `// TODO(T##): brief reason`

## After each change

Run: `make type-check`, `make lint`, `make build`

Add an Unreleased bullet to `CHANGELOG.md` if the change is user-visible.

## Branching (AI default)

- Create topic branch from main BEFORE changing files
- Format: `author/prefix/short-kebab-description` (lowercase)
- Do NOT run `git commit`, `git push`, or `gh pr create` unless the user explicitly asks

## Milestone

All new work → **26Q2** milestone
